race.comment: BALLISTIC BLAZE (3) got the job done again after running them ragged to make it two in a row, scoring at this track over 400m (22.85). Can continue on with her winning form. NIGHT SHARID (5) turned spotting a big start finishing sixth (25.93) last time in a Mix 6/7 at Ballarat. Form here at the trip excellent including two wins. Comes out of a solid form race last start. In the mix. SCOTCH FEVER (4) hit the ground running and was prominent throughout but faded out of it when 8th at this track in a Grade 6. In the mix. BENNACHIE LANE (2) is worth including.
